Writers Michael Moreci and Steve Seeley take over for series creator Tim Seeley, while Emilio Laiso illustrates and K Michael Russell colors the series.

description:
Exploding out of the pages of GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY, Sam Humphries is chronicling the adventures of Star-Lord when he's not with the Guardians. He's probably going to get in a lot of trouble. The series ended with issue 12 due to the Secret Wars event and was replaced by the Star-Lord & Kitty Pryde Secret Wars tie-in series. After Secret Wars, Peter Quill received a new ongoing series in Star-Lord Vol.1.

Collected Editions

  • Legendary Star-Lord: Face It, I Rule (#1-5)
  • Legendary Star-Lord: Rise of The Black Vortex (#6-12)
  • Legendary Star-Lord: Out of Orbit (#6-8)
  • Guardians of the Galaxy & X-Men: The Black Vortex (#9-11)

Translated into German & Spanish.
name: Legendary Star-Lord

description:
Rocket Raccoon's first solo ongoing series, written by Skottie Young. From the pages of the Guardians of the Galaxy come these new adventures of Rocket Raccoon. Just don't call him a raccoon. Rocket or Skottie. This is Rocket's first own ongoing series, but he had received a Rocket Raccoon mini-series years before. Altought the first issue was on the number 1 sales charts, Marvel continued the series for only 11 issues before it was replaced by the Groot series, which also starred Rocket.

Collected Editions

  • Rocket Raccoon: A Chasing Tale (#1-6)
  • Guardians of the Galaxy: All-New Marvel Treasury Edition (#1)
  • Rocket Raccoon: Storytailer (#7-11)
